column5: Anyone have a recommendation as to who would be good to use in the Kawartha area?  Thanks.
Did you catch a big'un Jeff?
advance taxidermy is not that far away and they have some very nice work if you can do your self a favor and take the trip over to them.

If your going to go out of your way and come down toward Toronto give Pro Line taxidermy, at Black creek and Jane a visit, Sylvio is one of the best around in my opinon, and his prices are tough to beat.  Paul
....Just a guess Glen but it might be this fatty.  Nice bass Jeff.
I missed that one some how Spiel.
The best i know is Jeff Brain on hwy 11 just south of orillia...  Ive got a deer head done by him and ive seen his fish mounts.. I know that he has won alot of awards for his mounts.
Jeff there's one in Havelock, can't think of the name but I'm sure it's in the phone book. Haven't had anything done but he's been around awhile...
A buddy of mine had some animals done at Pine Ridge Taxidermy on Cty rd 45 north of Cobourg south of Alderville.  He mentioned that they were pretty good.
Thanks for the good replies everyone  I will be calling tomorrow and get pricing.
